  "prompt": "How do I add more than one WordPress site in Godaddy's Deluxe hosting plan?",
  "response": "To add multiple WordPress sites on GoDaddy's Deluxe hosting plan, you'll need to follow these steps. GoDaddy's Deluxe plan allows you to host up to 10 websites, so you can set up multiple WordPress installations. Here's how to do it:\n\n1. **Access Your GoDaddy Account:**\n   - Log in to your GoDaddy account and go to the \"My Products\" section.\n   - Find your Deluxe Hosting plan and click on \"Manage\" next to it.\n\n2. **Install WordPress for the First Site:**\n   - If you haven't already installed WordPress for your primary site, you can do so using the one-click install feature.\n   - Navigate to the cPanel dashboard and look for the \"WordPress\" icon under the \"Website Builders\" section. Click on it to start the installation process.\n   - Follow the prompts to set up your first WordPress site.\n\n3. **Create a New Directory for Additional Sites:**\n   - To add another WordPress site, you need to create a new directory for it within your hosting account.\n   - Go to the cPanel and click on \"File Manager.\"\n   - Navigate to the `public_html` folder and create a new folder for your second site (e.g., `public_html/secondsite`).\n\n4. **Install WordPress in the New Directory:**\n   - Go back to the cPanel and initiate a new WordPress installation.\n   - During the installation process, select the directory you just created (`public_html/secondsite`) as the installation path.\n   - Complete the installation process with your new site's details.\n\n5. **Set Up Domain or Subdomain for New Site:**\n   - If you want to use a subdomain (e.g., `secondsite.yourdomain.com`), go to the \"Domains\" section in cPanel and set up the subdomain, pointing it to the new directory (`public_html/secondsite`).\n   - If you want to use a separate domain, you'll need to add it to your hosting account first and then point it to the appropriate directory.\n\n6. **Repeat for Additional Sites:**\n   - You can repeat the process for up to 10 sites, creating new directories and installing WordPress in each one as needed.\n\n7. **Manage Multiple WordPress Installations:**\n   - To manage all your WordPress sites, consider using a tool like the \"Installatron\" within cPanel, which can help you manage updates and backups across multiple installations.\n\n**Important Notes:**\n- Make sure your hosting plan supports the number of sites you want to add. Deluxe plans support up to 10 sites.\n- Be mindful of resource usage, as multiple sites can increase server load. Monitor your sites and consider upgrading your plan if needed.\n- Keep all your WordPress installations updated to ensure security and performance.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to host multiple WordPress sites on your GoDaddy Deluxe hosting plan. If you encounter any issues, GoDaddy's support team can provide further assistance.",
